title: Warriors sweep Yaks
text: Print this article Advertisement Walla Walla Community College’s volleyball team won all three sets against Yakima Valley with lopsided scores of 25-7, 25-13, and 25-14 in a Northwest Athletic Conference East Region match Wednesday at the Dietrich Dome. Photo by Michael Lopez Walla Walla Community College’s Amy Arnzen (above) spikes the ball against Yakima Valley Wednesday at the Dietrich Dome. The Warriors’ Taylor Hall scored eight kills, while Savannah Ruark had seven in their quick match at home. Dani Burke set 21 assists, and Amy Arnzen made 21 digs. Walla Walla next plays Friday in Pasco at Columbia Basin. More like this story
